wiki_description: White Spy is quite curious, which often lands him in various traps, he also has a weakness for pretty girls. He seems to frequently be lured into traps in which he was insulted or challenged by Black Spy, suggesting he may have a prideful streak. He threaten a civilian to gain their help, but he is often very polite or even sometimes even pays them afterward. He is also shown to be an avid reader falling for traps Black Spy themed around whatever book was being read or coming up with his own scheme based on his reading. He is also frequently seen reading in the magazine comics, as well.he is portrayed as being more well-received by the public, receiving medals, walking the red carpet, and even having a street publicly dedicated to him. It's shown that he loves dogs, to the point the Black Embassy based an entire plan around his love of dogs to infiltrate his safe. There are other multiple occasions where he can be seen with dogs.

related_topics.description: Black Spy tends to be more comical in his schemes against White Spy.He has been shown as being susceptible to baits involving games, food and attractive women. Black Spy has also incorporated civilians into his schemes, although he does not cause them harm, instead he has been shown as being empathetic towards other civilians, this sometimes exploited by White Spy. Black Spy occasionally uses disguises, and in comics by the same writer is portrayed as being envious as well as seeking of recognition and praise, often to his detriment.

Grey Spy (aka Lady in Grey) is a third spy appearing in some Spy vs Spy comic strip.Whenever she appears, she always manages to be successful in defeating both Black Spy and White Spy. Grey Spy is shown as being manipulative, occasionally tricking White and Black spies into making peace with each other before killing both of them.
